properties.abstract: The ideal tour for families and amblers or with the e-bike - this pleasant, easy single trail passes through woodland and offers wonderful views of Alvaschein lying 200 metres below. A very agreeable BBQ area invites you to take a break.
properties.description: This bike tour starts in Lenzerheide. The route takes the left side of the valley towards Lantsch/Lenz on country roads. On the way you can take in enjoyable glimpses of the valley and Oberhalbstein - in Romansch and also officially known as Surses. A sunny bench just before the village Rofna invites you to stop awhile. Again beautiful vistas open before the eyes with distant views of small hamlets in the valley - Lantsch/Lenz, Mon, Stierva, Mutten and Obermutten. Soon the next vantage point Crap la Tretscha appears. Don't miss the stop here. Along with the spectacular view of Alvaschein 200 metres below a very pleasant grilling area awaits you. Moving on a gentle rise along the valley floor takes you back to Lenzerheide.
